Wireless Network hardware

Wireless NIC --> Wireless Network Interface Card

Wireless Access Point --> has only one ethernet port at the back
					  --> his function is to act like a bridge between a wireless and ethernet network.
					  
Wireless SOHO --> has more ethernet port at the back.

AD-HOCK VS Infrastructure Mode
1. AD-HOCK --> doent need a Wireless Access Point
2. Infrastructure Mode --> Uses a WAP

NOTES 
	>> TO connect to a wireless network, your pc needs a wireless nic
	>> youre also need a wireless access point to which pc;s can connect
	>> many wireless access point are package with switch and routers.


